
The charAt() method returns the character at the specified index in a string.

The index of the first character is 0, the second character is 1, and so on.

Tip: The index of the last character in a string is string.length-1, the second last character is string.length-2,
and so on (See "More Examples").

Syntax
string.charAt(index)

Parameter:
index	Required. An integer representing the index of the character you want to return

Return Value:	A String, representing the character at the specified index, or an empty string if the index number
is not found

Example

Return the last character of a string:

var str = "HELLO WORLD";
var res = str.charAt(str.length-1);
console.log(res);

